    <item>
      <title>Re: Pointless and Useless Slows</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Shaman&amp;message.id=5470#M5470</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Maybe you should look outside the box at what the intended reason for each spell might be.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I'll mention Lingering sloth.&amp;nbsp; What you see on the surface is a spell that's only 25% of a slow.&amp;nbsp; So why would you want to use it.&amp;nbsp; Ever heard of first agro?&amp;nbsp; Cast this buff on a tank.&amp;nbsp; It lasts for approx 5 min (4.1 base time) and it procs a lot.&amp;nbsp; Shaman have for a long time whined about wanting to be the main healers in a group.&amp;nbsp; A lot of the talk wasn't just about how we couldn't function as one because our heals were too slow and&amp;nbsp; wouldn't heal enough, but also because if we were the main healer, we wouldn't be able to slow the mob in time to get the first heal off.&amp;nbsp; Malos is a 5 second base casting spell (3.4 for me with my focus' and blessing of devotion from a cleric) and combine that with a 3 second casting slow (TA is three second, or 2.1 using the spell, add another second for spell gems refreshment) and you have a tank that takes at almost 10 seconds of dmg before a heal can be cast on the tank....&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;However, add the sloth buff to the tank and what does this do?&amp;nbsp; First off, it's based on disease resists, which normally equal less resists than our magic based other slows.&amp;nbsp; But, it also has a -50 resist modifier, making it extra easy to land.&amp;nbsp; Because the proc is based on the mob hitting the person, it's free agro for the tank, and a free slow and its very likely to go off the second that the mob hits the tank.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;What this boils down to, is that the mob is then slowed by the tank faster than it would take you to cast slow on the mob.&amp;nbsp; This gives the shaman the ability to main heal in a group and not have to cast slow, or it gives the shaman the ability to main heal and slow, but you would&amp;nbsp; have a little bit extra time to land another slow, and more time to heal just in case it's needed.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I think that it's a very nice spell.&amp;nbsp; I use it periodically.&amp;nbsp; It enables me to take on a purely dps role in a group if I wanted to, althoug most of the time I cast my TA slow since it's free as well.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I can comment on the other slow, but I honestly do not use it a lot.&amp;nbsp; I have found one fight that it worked very nicely for, but other than that, I haven't seen one yet.&amp;nbsp; If you get any spell in DoD.. get Lingering Sloth.&amp;nbsp; It's very much worth it.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Mon, 07 Nov 2005 04:55:13 GMT</pubDate>
      <author>Valsuvious</author>
