    <item>
      <title>Re: Pointless and Useless Slows</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Shaman&amp;message.id=5471#M5471</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;If you think the use for this spell lies in getting a early slow on in exp groups to enable you to heal better, you are sadly mistaken.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;A 25% slow that procs every&amp;nbsp;7 seconds on average isn't going to do a whole lot. You still have to slow the mob, just as if Sloth wasn't there or you'll end up falling behind, since our heals are balanced around a 75% slow. Second, the damage reduction from a 25% slow is miserable when you account for the mitigation and you have no guarantee it will go off before you actually landed your slow to begin with.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The obvious use for the spell is to slow multiple targets beating on your tank, but for that I might as well use Vindictive Spirit, which not only is more effctive(50%), but also lands much better. On top of that it will provide a mitigation buff up to 1600 HPs. See, this is the classic situation where one spell that terribly sucks, makes another spell, that has its issues and which I have pointed out in other threads, look incredibly good.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;If a developer actually took the time to look into what Sloth effectively does in groups, they couldn't but up the effectiveness on it. We Shamans tend to be way too complacent or would you want to compare this spell's power with the Druid's reptile buff?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;There are 2 possible changes that this spell requires to be of use, yet I doubt it will happen, because in today's EQ it takes a star lawyer to change things to the better once they go live:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1) Up the % on Lingering Sloth to trigger to 75%. It only lasts 3 ticks, anyway.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2) Keep Lingering Sloth at 25%, mitigated, but make it stack with our other slows. Shamans have been asking for a less mitigated slow for a long time, adding another 12% would achieve the same thing, but require the mob to be vulnerable to magic and disease and to proc it constantly. If you were worried about trivializing content that does not contain slow mitigation, then put a hard cap on slows.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
